- This is ridiculous.

19:00.599 --> 19:04.686
Literally, no one understands me,
so I'm just gonna just be on my way.

19:04.770 --> 19:07.314
Okay. Are we done?

19:07.397 --> 19:10.442
No. No, we're not done.
Can I have a job application?

19:10.526 --> 19:14.571
Even after she ghosted me...

19:14.655 --> 19:16.698
I still keep them.

19:18.033 --> 19:21.453
It's contact lenses.
It's pretty gross, actually.

19:31.046 --> 19:32.589
Nick, Marcos.

19:32.673 --> 19:33.924
- Bump up.
- The usual?

19:34.007 --> 19:36.593
- Yeah, make it a triple.
- Shitty day?

19:36.677 --> 19:39.847
Yeah. Eviction notice.

19:39.930 --> 19:43.141
- I wouldn't say terrible.
- We have 30 days to open.

19:43.225 --> 19:45.310
Our entire livelihood is in danger.

19:45.394 --> 19:47.437
I don't know how I'm gonna feed
my pregnant wife,

19:47.521 --> 19:49.773
but other than that, it's pretty good.

19:49.857 --> 19:53.068
Welcome to the hospitality industry.
Basically a slow death.

19:53.151 --> 19:55.737
Are you Asian Gordon Ramsay?
Why would you say that?

19:55.821 --> 19:57.573
- Get out.
- Fine, I will.

19:57.656 --> 20:01.785
I have to explain to my pregnant wife that
we're not gonna have money in two weeks.

20:01.869 --> 20:03.787
- I'm gonna pay you.
- I know you will.

20:03.871 --> 20:05.455
- You complete me.
- Goodbye.

20:05.539 --> 20:06.999
- Bye.
- Bye-bye, little Kimchi Taco.

20:07.082 --> 20:08.166
- Goodbye.
- Later.

20:08.250 --> 20:12.546
Goodbye. Don't touch me.
Where's the nearest bridge? Anybody?

20:18.844 --> 20:22.764
You'll like it here.
Yeah, the chef is supposed to be good.

20:28.187 --> 20:31.857
It's okay. Just gonna have a conversation.

20:32.858 --> 20:34.318
Yeah.

20:35.319 --> 20:36.737
Okay.

20:37.738 --> 20:40.657
You got this. Okay.

20:42.326 --> 20:43.452
Thank you.

20:46.079 --> 20:48.123
Excuse me. Can I help you?

20:48.207 --> 20:52.002
Hey, girl. Cute dress.
I'm just meeting a friend.

20:52.085 --> 20:56.215
- What friend?
- Those ones. Over there. That's my friend.

20:56.298 --> 20:58.467
- Oh, shit.
- That guy just saw you and ducked.

20:58.550 --> 21:00.636
No, no, no. He just dropped his menu.

21:00.719 --> 21:04.640
- I just gotta talk to him for five minutes.
- I'm sorry. I can't let you do that.

21:05.807 --> 21:08.852
Oh, hey, I know that guy. Adolfo-Nick.
What's up, dude?

21:08.936 --> 21:10.687
- Hey.
- Yo. You know her?

21:10.771 --> 21:13.565
- It's a long story.
- Ma'am, I have to ask you to leave.

21:13.649 --> 21:16.235
"Ma'am"? We're the same age. You can relax.

21:16.318 --> 21:18.529
- You're carrying a garbage bag.
- Yeah.

21:18.612 --> 21:23.492
And you tell people where to sit
for a living. And your dress is undone.

21:27.120 --> 21:28.914
Unhandle me! What the...?

21:28.997 --> 21:32.251
- I care for you so much.
- Let go of me!

21:32.334 --> 21:36.338
- Okay. You can let me go.
- That's the craziest thing I've ever seen.

21:36.421 --> 21:39.299
I had it under control until you interfered.

21:39.383 --> 21:42.594
You magically show up everywhere.
Are you my stalker?

21:42.678 --> 21:46.557
I think the words
you're looking for are "thank you."

21:46.640 --> 21:49.560
And then I say, "You're welcome."

21:50.561 --> 21:51.478
I'm Lucy.

21:52.479 --> 21:54.606
Charmed, I'm sure.

21:56.567 --> 21:58.610
You good, Lucy?

21:59.611 --> 22:01.738
- Yeah, yeah. No, I'm okay.
- Okay.

22:01.822 --> 22:03.907
I'm just processing it. Wait. Wait.

22:03.991 --> 22:06.201
Hey, hello. What?

22:06.285 --> 22:09.246
You just manhandled me, and you're gonna
just leave me alone on the street?

22:09.329 --> 22:12.291
Hey! Hey! You hit her? You just hit her?

22:12.374 --> 22:13.417
- No, no, no.
- No.

22:13.500 --> 22:15.210
I see what's going on. You just hit her.

22:15.294 --> 22:17.087
- No.
- Okay. That's cool, man!

22:17.171 --> 22:19.047
- You hit a lady. That's nice.
- No, no, no.

22:19.131 --> 22:20.591
- I didn't hit her.
- This is my fault.

22:20.674 --> 22:21.884
This is not your fault.

22:21.967 --> 22:27.890
Being a woman is like living in a goddamn
nobody-believes-me movie every day, okay?

22:27.973 --> 22:31.310
But today is not that day
because we are gonna fight him.

22:31.393 --> 22:32.686
- Come at me, homey.
- I really...

22:32.769 --> 22:33.729
- Come at me!
- Oh, no.

22:33.812 --> 22:36.523
- Oh, my God. Fuck!
- You come at me!

22:36.607 --> 22:38.233
This is all your fault.

22:38.317 --> 22:40.944
I'm so sorry.
We should get some ice on that.

22:41.028 --> 22:43.030
Here's an idea:
Why don't you leave me alone?

22:43.113 --> 22:46.074
No. Only a terrible person would
leave you alone in your time of need.

22:46.158 --> 22:49.036
Yeah. And I think
you are that terrible person.

22:49.119 --> 22:50.329
No. I'm nice.

22:50.412 --> 22:53.332
If you got to know me,
you'd be obsessed with me.

23:00.422 --> 23:05.135
Oh, great. Okay, the car was just pre-game.
This is where you actually murder me.

23:05.219 --> 23:08.847
- And yet you are still following me.
- What? You're a squatter?

23:08.931 --> 23:10.891
- I guess so.
- Construction worker?

23:10.974 --> 23:12.976
- Sometimes.
- Are we playing 20 questions?

23:13.060 --> 23:14.728
- If you must know...
- I must.

23:14.811 --> 23:17.940
It's an old YMCA,
and I'm turning it into a boutique hotel.

23:18.023 --> 23:20.359
- What? You're serious?
- Yes.

23:20.442 --> 23:22.069
Welcome to the Chloe Hotel.

23:22.152 --> 23:25.989
I'm building a place that feels
like the spots I fell in love with

23:26.073 --> 23:27.407
when I first moved to New York.

23:27.491 --> 23:29.952
Those little places that only exist here.

23:30.035 --> 23:31.578
But I've spent five years,

23:31.662 --> 23:38.001
and, as you can see, every cent
that I have, and it's all falling to shit.

23:38.085 --> 23:40.295
So, what are you gonna do?

23:40.379 --> 23:43.924
Looks like it's coming together.
Is this gonna be the lobby?

23:44.925 --> 23:46.593
Nothing gets by you.

23:47.594 --> 23:49.513
What's gonna happen up there?

23:49.596 --> 23:52.182
That's phase two.
I can't afford to touch it right now.

23:54.893 --> 23:57.604
- Still hurts?
- Yeah. Just a bit.

23:57.688 --> 24:00.607
- Wait. You're doing it wrong. Give it to me.
- How am I doing it wrong?

24:00.691 --> 24:03.026
Can't have ice touching the skin.
You need a middleman.

24:04.820 --> 24:06.488
Okay. Do you want whiskey?

24:06.572 --> 24:08.448
Yes, please.

24:13.078 --> 24:14.955
She really got you good, huh?

24:15.038 --> 24:17.875
Yeah. She sure did.

24:17.958 --> 24:22.504
Here. This will cure what ails you.

24:24.381 --> 24:28.802
Wow, whiskey really is
Mother Nature's painkiller, huh?

24:29.803 --> 24:32.181
What have you got in here, Lucy?

24:33.182 --> 24:34.183
Oh, my God.

24:34.266 --> 24:35.559
An espresso machine?

24:35.642 --> 24:38.020
- Don't go too deep.
- And a sock.

24:38.103 --> 24:39.438
- <i>Cat in the Hat.</i>
- Okay.

24:39.521 --> 24:42.608
- Yep.
- Oh, my God. Are those toenail clippings?

24:42.691 --> 24:45.652
You've seen quite enough, mister. Yeah.

24:45.736 --> 24:47.404
- I'm gonna...
- Oh, my God.

24:47.487 --> 24:51.033
- Thanks for coming.
- I get it. You're a pessimist.

24:52.701 --> 24:55.662
That is the worst thing
anyone has ever said to me.

24:55.746 --> 25:01.251
You collect these things in anticipation
that your relationships are going to end.

25:01.335 --> 25:02.169
- No.
- It's crazy.

25:02.252 --> 25:05.380
No, no, no. You're wrong.
They're a celebration of memories.

25:05.464 --> 25:07.174
- You're a hoarder.
- I'm not a hoarder.

25:07.257 --> 25:10.177
- Hoarder. Hoarder.
- Take it back. I'm not a hoarder. Stop!

25:10.260 --> 25:13.388
You want evidence that your relationships
existed in the first place.

25:14.389 --> 25:17.768
Are you afraid that you won't remember
the guys you dated?

25:19.061 --> 25:21.313
I don't need to explain myself to you.

25:21.396 --> 25:25.609
How about you? You've never collected
anything from a past relationship?

25:25.692 --> 25:27.486
No. I'm a minimalist.

25:27.569 --> 25:30.989
I can fit everything I own
inside a backpack.

25:31.073 --> 25:33.617
When the zombie apocalypse comes, I'm out.

25:33.700 --> 25:36.245
Nice. You're one of those.

25:36.328 --> 25:37.996
Yeah. One of...

25:38.080 --> 25:39.665
- One of what?
- You know.

25:39.748 --> 25:42.125
"I'm a lone wolf. I don't need anybody."

25:42.209 --> 25:44.503
But really you are just scared
of showing your insides.

25:44.586 --> 25:48.090
Yeah. Everyone either leaves,
disappoints or dies.

25:48.173 --> 25:52.344
Okay, Mr. Rogers. Can't wait
for the new show: <i>Uplift the Nation.</i>

25:52.427 --> 25:55.305
So funny. What are you gonna do
with this stuff?

25:56.974 --> 25:58.684
That's a good question.

25:59.685 --> 26:02.813
When love crumbles,
how do you preserve its ruins?

26:04.231 --> 26:07.359
- Why don't you leave it here?
- What? No.

26:07.442 --> 26:08.735
- Come on.
- No, I can't do that.

26:08.819 --> 26:11.280
- Just let go.
- No, no, no. It's okay.

26:11.363 --> 26:13.866
- Sure. It'll be okay.
- Okay.

26:14.867 --> 26:16.410
This...

26:16.493 --> 26:19.997
Oh, look. It's a nail. Perfectly placed.

26:20.998 --> 26:22.833
Would you look at that?

26:27.462 --> 26:29.214
Kind of looks cool.

26:29.298 --> 26:31.383
It's like art in a gallery.

26:31.466 --> 26:33.135
The Sad Gallery.

26:33.218 --> 26:36.763
More like the Broken Heart Gallery.

26:38.307 --> 26:40.058
Do you have a marker?

26:41.059 --> 26:43.854
- What?
- You have a marker, I just...

26:43.937 --> 26:45.230
- No, I don't.
- Come on. Please.

26:45.314 --> 26:47.232
- I have a brilliant idea.
- Why do you want it?

26:47.316 --> 26:50.152
I'm feeling inspired. Let me express.

26:53.238 --> 26:54.740
Think fast.

26:55.741 --> 26:56.992
Nice.

26:57.075 --> 27:00.871
Oh, sure. Draw on the wall.

27:22.851 --> 27:25.812
Thank you for letting me express myself.

27:25.896 --> 27:27.689
You're welcome.

27:30.359 --> 27:33.946
Wait. What's the security like
in this place?

27:34.029 --> 27:35.697
Is there security?

27:35.781 --> 27:38.700
You're worried that someone is gonna
break into my unfinished hotel

27:38.784 --> 27:40.494
and steal your ex-boyfriend's tie?

27:40.577 --> 27:42.788
No. That won't happen, right?

27:42.871 --> 27:45.290
- No, it wouldn't happen.
- No.

27:45.374 --> 27:47.668
No, you're right. I should leave it.

27:47.751 --> 27:49.503
Yeah, I can leave this.

27:49.586 --> 27:53.173
It'll be good. I'm... I'm gonna leave it.

27:53.257 --> 27:55.968
No. I can't, actual... No.

27:56.051 --> 27:58.679
- What? You're looking at me.
- I'm not. What?

27:58.762 --> 28:01.557
- I'm sorry. This just got weird.
- It's okay.

28:01.640 --> 28:06.311
No, I'm... I'm gonna go. But I will... Bye.

28:07.771 --> 28:10.399
- Bye.
- He was my high school sweetheart.

28:10.482 --> 28:13.443
He moved across the country,
and we lost touch.

28:13.527 --> 28:17.281
But smoked too much weed, wouldn't call
you back. He would be a terrible husband.

28:17.364 --> 28:19.616
I make my husband wear it when we ****.

28:20.617 --> 28:22.452
Lucy? Babe?

28:22.536 --> 28:23.579
Are you okay?

28:23.662 --> 28:25.163
Maybe you could try to get a job?

28:25.247 --> 28:26.540
My birthday week is coming up,

28:26.623 --> 28:28.876
and I expect a really thoughtful
and expensive gift.

28:28.959 --> 28:31.879
- There's no birthday week.
- Yes. It's the week of your birthday.

28:31.962 --> 28:33.547
You're not a 16th-century monarch.

28:33.630 --> 28:37.259
You can't command multiple days
for your personal festivities.

28:37.342 --> 28:39.136
Remember our Monopoly tournaments?

28:39.219 --> 28:41.930
Well, I need a Get Out Of Jail Free card.

28:42.931 --> 28:46.685
Anyway, last night, it was rough.

28:47.686 --> 28:49.771
I wish I could talk to you about it.

28:50.772 --> 28:51.607
Bye.

28:53.483 --> 28:55.027
Lucy.

28:56.445 --> 28:57.613
Nick?

28:57.696 --> 28:58.906
Can I come in?

28:59.907 --> 29:04.036
No. No, no, no. Lucy is dead.

29:04.119 --> 29:05.746
How'd she die?

29:05.829 --> 29:08.081
- Decapitated on a roller coaster.
- That's a shame.

29:08.165 --> 29:09.958
She had such a nice head.

29:13.212 --> 29:15.005
And you are not wearing any pants.

29:17.424 --> 29:20.010
Pants. No. Not wearing those.

29:21.970 --> 29:23.555
Shoelaces in a bag?

29:24.556 --> 29:26.266
Go ahead. Judge me.

29:26.350 --> 29:27.976
No judgments.

29:28.060 --> 29:32.481
- Wait. What are you doing here?
- I wanna show you something. Come on.

29:32.564 --> 29:34.900
- How did you get in here?
- Your roommates let me in.

29:34.983 --> 29:37.027
Those bitches.

29:44.451 --> 29:48.664
Okay. So this map was just here
when you showed up this morning?

29:48.747 --> 29:50.791
- Yep.
- Who could have left it?

29:50.874 --> 29:53.877
I know a construction worker,
a delivery guy,

29:53.961 --> 29:56.839
one of your multiple personalities?

29:56.922 --> 29:58.423
This is amazing.

29:58.507 --> 30:03.971
There are broken people out there like me,
people who need to let go and move on.

30:04.054 --> 30:07.182
Good. Well, you can take the stuff
and move on.

30:07.266 --> 30:11.228
There's nowhere else like this.
I wish someone had done this for me.

30:11.311 --> 30:13.897
The Broken Heart Gallery could be
a community service.

30:13.981 --> 30:15.274
No. This is my hotel.

30:15.357 --> 30:19.820
It is not some sort of Lost and Found
for hoarder stalkers.

30:19.903 --> 30:21.947
- Again, not a hoarder.
- Hoarder.

30:22.030 --> 30:23.740
No. We've been through this.

30:23.824 --> 30:26.535
Oh, wow, this is the shrine to exes
you were talking about?

30:26.618 --> 30:27.870
I didn't say... I...

30:27.953 --> 30:29.913
- It's a direct quote.
- I didn't say that.

30:29.997 --> 30:31.707
Lucy, this is my friend Marcos.

30:31.790 --> 30:33.876
Hey. Oh, my God. We're friends now?

30:33.959 --> 30:37.421
That would explain why I'm building
a bar top for you for free.

30:37.504 --> 30:39.923
- Can you not...? Don't listen to him.
- Friendship. Servitude.

30:40.007 --> 30:42.968
I am the godfather to his unborn child.

30:43.051 --> 30:46.221
No, he's lobbying
for the position of godfather.

30:46.305 --> 30:50.058
Plot twist: It's not going well.
If I had to guess, you know?

30:50.142 --> 30:52.603
Would you want this man
to be your spiritual guide?

30:52.686 --> 30:54.980
No. Maybe my TV guide.

30:55.063 --> 30:56.899
- Am I right?
- Terrible dad joke.

30:56.982 --> 30:58.400
I like her. Let's get to work.

30:58.483 --> 30:59.610
- Okay.
- Nice to meet you.

30:59.693 --> 31:02.237
Wait. Wait, wait, wait.

31:02.321 --> 31:04.448
I can help. I...

31:05.449 --> 31:08.118
I can help with the hotel
in exchange for gallery space.

31:08.202 --> 31:09.661
- No.
- No, I can help.

31:09.745 --> 31:15.083
I can... I can paint. I can saw.
I can lift and lay tile, grout.

31:15.167 --> 31:16.793
- Is that...? That's a thing.
- Yeah.

31:16.877 --> 31:18.128
It's not gonna happen.

31:18.212 --> 31:22.674
That sounds like free labor,
and, Nick, you love free labor, don't you?

31:22.758 --> 31:23.675
You do. Come on.

31:23.759 --> 31:26.094
- Come on.
- You don't have a plan for the balcony yet.

31:26.178 --> 31:30.057
I did say I had a plan for the balcony.
I said it was phase two.

31:30.140 --> 31:32.601
Sorry, balconies are really important.

31:32.684 --> 31:34.102
- He gets it.
- They're essential.

31:34.186 --> 31:36.522
- What is going on?
- Two people agreeing.

31:36.605 --> 31:39.608
- Maybe eternal friendship. I don't know.
- We're bonding. We're friends?

31:39.691 --> 31:41.485
We should take it step by step, but sure.

31:41.568 --> 31:42.986
- Okay.
- It's a good start.

31:43.070 --> 31:44.988
- I hate both of you.
- Is that a yes?

31:45.072 --> 31:46.573
- No. No.
- Hell, yes.

31:46.657 --> 31:49.660
Of course. We could use the help.
You start tomorrow, 7 in the morning.

31:49.743 --> 31:52.287
Get us the coffee, right?
You know, gotta pay the piper.

31:52.371 --> 31:55.582
We do love oat milk. You can get almond milk
if you don't have it.

31:55.666 --> 32:00.045
Soy milk, whatever. Have fun with it.
But nothing with actual dairy.

32:00.128 --> 32:01.839
He gets really sensitive in his tummy.

32:01.922 --> 32:04.842
- Okay. All right. Let's...
- He has IBS, it's embarrassing.

32:04.925 --> 32:06.343
- IBS is a real thing.
- Stop it.

32:06.426 --> 32:09.721
- Tell me more about his tummy.
- This is not happening. There is no tummy.

32:09.805 --> 32:11.139
Goodbye.

32:11.223 --> 32:13.517
- Dude. What? No.
- We have 30 days. We need help.

32:52.472 --> 32:54.141
This is Morris.

32:54.224 --> 32:56.476
My husband and I got him together.

32:56.560 --> 32:57.895
My husband left.

32:58.896 --> 33:01.190
Morris took it pretty hard.

33:02.191 --> 33:04.568
Yeah, he died immediately.

33:06.111 --> 33:10.991
Let me get this straight. You are collecting
other people's junk in addition to your own?

33:12.409 --> 33:15.370
Oh, shut up, Jeff.
I should text Max about this.

33:15.454 --> 33:17.748
- He likes to be up to date with galleries.
- No.

33:17.831 --> 33:20.167
- Don't do that.
- You're right. I'll slide in the DMs.

33:20.250 --> 33:22.586
- That's more chill.
- You need to get a grip.

33:22.669 --> 33:24.963
He is dating a doctor
with the face of an angel.

33:25.047 --> 33:26.381
You're a monster.

33:26.465 --> 33:29.551
Thank you.
Okay, you need some sexual Listerine.

33:29.635 --> 33:30.969
Jeff agrees.

33:31.053 --> 33:33.847
What about that new guy, Nick?

33:33.931 --> 33:37.935
Last time I slept with someone
I worked with, it ended very badly.

33:38.018 --> 33:40.521
Oh, my God. That is so true, Jeff.
That does sound like progress.

33:40.604 --> 33:41.438
Thank you.

33:41.522 --> 33:44.942
Why don't you invite your "friend" Nick
to my birthday?

33:45.025 --> 33:47.986
I came up with a new theme, murder karaoke.

33:48.070 --> 33:50.072
It combines my favorite things,
murder and karaoke.

33:50.155 --> 33:51.990
- A heavenly combo.
- A perfect combination.

33:52.074 --> 33:54.451
You guys.

33:54.535 --> 33:56.245
I am in love.

33:56.328 --> 33:59.915
Her name is Irina, and she's got
tiny baby bones like a baby chick,

33:59.998 --> 34:03.752
and I just wanna build a nest for her
and chew her food for her and feed her.

34:03.836 --> 34:05.462
Jesus, I give it two weeks.

34:05.546 --> 34:09.007
Do I detect cynicism
from the great believer of love?

34:09.091 --> 34:11.927
She's right. You've banged
more Russian models than a tech billionaire.

34:12.010 --> 34:14.137
- If you were a guy, we would hate you.
- Yeah.

34:14.221 --> 34:15.764
- I don't need this.
- Yes, you do.

34:15.848 --> 34:19.893
- No, I don't. No, I don't. Okay.
- Yes, you do. Eat the pasta.

34:23.355 --> 34:25.774
Hey, Nick, I...

34:26.775 --> 34:29.695
- I can't work anymore this week, dude.
- Why?

34:29.777 --> 34:35.117
Your homeboy's been commissioned to build
a new table for that hotel in Fort Green.

34:35.199 --> 34:37.661
Really? That place is so cheesy.

34:37.744 --> 34:40.956
Oh, my God. How dare I take their money
when you don't like their mason jars.

34:41.039 --> 34:42.708
Look, man, I know...

34:42.791 --> 34:46.043
I know things are tough,
but I have a meeting at the bank on Friday,

34:46.128 --> 34:48.045
and I will get you your money.

34:48.130 --> 34:50.549
- You are first on my list.
- Oh, there's a list?

34:50.632 --> 34:52.759
Can I see the list, or...?

34:52.842 --> 34:55.262
- It's a theoretical list. Nick...
- It's gonna happen.

34:55.344 --> 34:57.472
- Come on.
- I can't keep doing this, man.

34:57.556 --> 35:01.310
I got a family. All right?
I have responsibilities. I'm sorry.

35:02.311 --> 35:04.646
Don't shut off on me. I...

35:04.730 --> 35:06.440
Show me those blushy cheeks.

35:06.523 --> 35:09.401
Oh, my God. I just feel so warm inside
when I see them. Show me...

35:09.484 --> 35:11.695
I'm fine, man. Please, just go, okay?

35:11.778 --> 35:13.363
All right.

35:13.447 --> 35:16.825
Good morning, building buds!
Who's ready to work?

35:16.909 --> 35:18.327
Because I am. Check me out.

35:18.410 --> 35:20.996
Look at this belt,
a practical belt for tools.

35:21.997 --> 35:24.917
- Here is your coffee, Marky Mark.
- All right, Lucy Liu.

35:25.918 --> 35:29.338
- And then, for you, I got the special milks.
- Thank you.

35:30.339 --> 35:31.381
- Dude.
- Sorry.

35:31.465 --> 35:35.469
Her Majesty looks a little upset
this morning, so tread lightly.

35:35.552 --> 35:39.765
Oh, no. We need to talk about our feelings?
Because the CFO has arrived.

35:39.848 --> 35:41.683
Chief Feelings Officer is here.

35:41.767 --> 35:45.145
- Let's hold hands. Okay, bring it in, guys.
- God. Dad jokes. Okay, I'm out.

35:45.229 --> 35:46.355
- See you, dude.
- Bye.

35:48.023 --> 35:49.983
- Who is that?
- Yeah, you're in the right place.

35:51.026 --> 35:52.945
- Hi.
- Hey.

35:53.946 --> 35:57.824
- Are you here for the Broken Heart Gallery?
- Yeah. Is this that heartbreak thing?

35:57.908 --> 36:01.161
Yeah. You're in the right place.
Welcome. I'm Lucy, head curator.

36:01.245 --> 36:02.829
Yeah. Willhelmina.

36:02.913 --> 36:04.915
So how's this whole thing work?

36:04.998 --> 36:07.835
I don't know.
How does this whole thing work?

36:07.918 --> 36:12.214
Well, why don't you we start
by you telling me what you brought and why?

36:12.297 --> 36:16.635
Yeah. Well, met my ex, Gina,
while I was actually...

36:16.718 --> 36:17.803
Oh, wait. Pause.

36:17.886 --> 36:20.097
Do you mind if I record this?

36:20.180 --> 36:22.766
- Just, you know, for our socials.
- Yeah. Sure.

36:22.850 --> 36:24.434
Take a step back against this.

36:24.518 --> 36:26.228
- Right. Here?
- Ooh, that is perfect.

36:26.311 --> 36:27.771
And go.

36:27.855 --> 36:29.356
I was in the hospital.

36:29.439 --> 36:32.192
I was recovering
from a pretty nasty skydiving accident.

36:32.276 --> 36:35.779
She was my nurse
and had a body cast covered all my tats,

36:35.863 --> 36:38.323
so Gina, she drew these ones on for me.

36:38.407 --> 36:40.367
When I could walk, I asked her to marry me.

36:40.450 --> 36:42.536
But then she changed her mind
three weeks later.

36:42.619 --> 36:44.788
- No.
- Damn, Gina.

36:44.872 --> 36:46.373
Anyway, time passed,

36:46.456 --> 36:51.211
but this just sat in the corner
of my bedroom, taunting me.

36:51.295 --> 36:56.758
- How long have you held on to it for?
- Six... Five years. Five years.

36:56.842 --> 37:00.846
Feels good to admit that, you know?
Then I heard about this place, so...

37:00.929 --> 37:03.515
And how exactly did you hear
about this place?

37:03.599 --> 37:06.685
- My masseuse's Instagram.
- And how did your masseuse hear about it?

37:06.768 --> 37:09.688
Don't listen to him.
Are you ready to hand it over?

37:09.771 --> 37:12.399
- Yeah. Yeah, I'm ready.
- Okay.

37:13.400 --> 37:15.152
It has an odor.

37:15.235 --> 37:16.904
Okay.

37:16.987 --> 37:18.363
- You did it.
- I did it.

37:18.447 --> 37:19.740
How does it feel?

37:19.823 --> 37:24.786
This is the first time in, like, five years
that I feel a little lighter.

37:24.870 --> 37:26.330
- Really?
- Yeah.

37:26.413 --> 37:29.208
That's amazing. Thank you.

37:29.291 --> 37:32.628
If you ever wanna see this again,
you can visit any time.

37:32.711 --> 37:34.713
- It'll be in my care, right here.
- Okay.

37:34.796 --> 37:37.716
Or, perhaps, at another location.

37:37.799 --> 37:40.385
No, definitely at this location.
Don't worry about him.

37:40.469 --> 37:43.388
- Who is he?
- Just one last thing.

37:43.472 --> 37:46.058
We just ask for a small donation.

37:46.141 --> 37:48.519
- Just to keep the gallery going.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

37:48.602 --> 37:51.772
There you go. It's only 5 bucks.
It's all I have.

37:51.855 --> 37:53.357
- Perfect.
- All right.

37:53.440 --> 37:55.067
Thank you so much.

37:57.194 --> 37:58.654
We're in business, baby.

37:58.737 --> 38:02.366
And Bonus Jonas, I'm making you clams.

38:03.992 --> 38:05.994
I'm going to take this.

38:12.000 --> 38:13.210
Thing about breakups is,

38:13.293 --> 38:15.963
someone can ruin your life
just by disappearing, you know?

38:16.046 --> 38:19.174
And then you hang on to the hope
that they'll barrel through your door

38:19.258 --> 38:22.761
full of believable explanations
as to why they didn't actually ghost you,

38:22.845 --> 38:25.806
or lose your number,
or just stop loving you.

38:25.889 --> 38:29.810
So what my ex left was a jar
of organic Choconut.

38:29.893 --> 38:33.272
So, heartbroken,
I would spoon it little by little

38:33.355 --> 38:36.650
while listening to Michael Bolton's
"When I'm Back On My Feet Again."

38:36.733 --> 38:38.235
It's rancid now.

38:38.318 --> 38:41.530
Kind of like my ex-girlfriend's soul.
I hate you. Just kidding.

38:41.613 --> 38:42.739
I hope you die.

38:42.823 --> 38:44.032
How do you get over someone?

38:44.116 --> 38:46.869
You just press some button on your body
and morph into a cyborg?

38:46.952 --> 38:50.163
Just keep going.
Don't look back, don't dwell on anything.

38:50.247 --> 38:52.291
Okay, so you just bottle everything up

38:52.374 --> 38:55.294
until you implode
in a fiery act of self-destruction?

38:55.377 --> 38:58.422
No. I manage my expectations.

39:04.845 --> 39:06.263
Marcos took another job.

39:06.346 --> 39:09.308
Our interior designer quit last week,
but I'm fine.

39:09.391 --> 39:10.893
I'm not upset. Why?

39:10.976 --> 39:15.355
Because I saw it coming a mile away
and I managed my expectations.

39:15.439 --> 39:20.152
Okay, so you don't ask anything of anyone,
which is why you're not asking me right now.

39:21.153 --> 39:24.239
- Asking you what?
- I'll be your interior designer.

39:24.323 --> 39:25.574
- Come on!
- Good God.

39:25.657 --> 39:28.785
Designer is just a fancy word for curator.
Or it's the other way around.

39:28.869 --> 39:31.788
I don't know, but regardless,
there's cool stuff all around us.

39:31.872 --> 39:33.790
You just need someone
to help you look for it.

39:33.874 --> 39:37.336
<i>Okay, but cool stuff means expensive,
and I'm pretty much broke.</i>

39:37.419 --> 39:41.340
<i>The key to collecting is seeing value
where others usually don't.</i>

39:41.423 --> 39:44.051
<i>You know, one lady's trash is
another lady's treasure.</i>

39:44.134 --> 39:45.552
<i>Kind of like relationships.</i>

39:45.636 --> 39:48.388
<i>And where might one find these treasures?</i>

39:48.472 --> 39:49.723
<i>Well, it is moving day.</i>

39:49.806 --> 39:51.975
First day of the month,
leases start and end,

39:52.059 --> 39:55.646
so New Yorkers are leaving pure gold
out on these streets.

39:55.729 --> 39:58.524
She's cute, she's charming,
she's calling my name.

39:58.607 --> 40:02.402
- She looks like rats live inside of her.
- Then she's habitable.

40:02.486 --> 40:06.073
Lucy, it's 40 blocks to the Chloe.
We are... We're not walking.

40:07.074 --> 40:09.660
Welcome to the nonviolent firearms show.

40:09.743 --> 40:10.661
Oh, my God.

40:10.744 --> 40:13.747
How do I seem to find myself
in this predicament?

40:18.293 --> 40:20.838
I'm tired. Can we take a break?

40:20.921 --> 40:23.131
Absolutely not. This was your idea.

40:23.215 --> 40:26.343
Fine, but can you distract me?
Tell me your life story.

40:26.426 --> 40:28.428
- My life story?
- Yeah.

40:28.512 --> 40:30.180
But my life hasn't even happened yet.

40:30.264 --> 40:33.141
Don't you ever think about
what you're gonna tell your biographer?

40:34.142 --> 40:37.563
- Is that something you think about?
- All the time. It'll begin as such:

40:37.646 --> 40:39.815
"It all started
on a sticky August afternoon."

40:39.898 --> 40:42.693
Oh, my God. Lucy, stop. Stop it.

40:42.776 --> 40:45.654
Okay. Your life story. Go.

40:46.655 --> 40:48.740
- Really?
- Yes.

40:50.450 --> 40:54.329
My parents really never settled down.
We moved a ton.

40:54.413 --> 40:56.081
That must have been hard.

40:56.164 --> 40:59.168
Think it make... Made me independent.

40:59.251 --> 41:01.712
So where would you go on holidays?

41:01.795 --> 41:03.422
Grandma's house.

41:04.423 --> 41:06.258
Tell me more about G-Ma.

41:06.341 --> 41:11.013
Well, she lived in this little place
called Kenosha, which is in Wisconsin.

41:11.096 --> 41:13.056
She looked like a Keebler elf.

41:13.140 --> 41:17.978
My grandma loved two things,
football and boxing.

41:18.061 --> 41:20.355
- She chewed tobacco till she was 90.
- Nice.

41:20.439 --> 41:23.108
And I always thought
she was this sweet old grandma,

41:23.192 --> 41:26.111
but it turns out
she was a bookie her entire life.

41:26.195 --> 41:29.323
- Okay, Grandma.
- I know. What a badass!

41:29.406 --> 41:33.076
After she died, they found
a wad of cash under her mattress.

41:34.077 --> 41:35.579
And she left it for me.

41:35.662 --> 41:38.624
- So that's what you used to start the Chloe.
- Yeah.

41:38.707 --> 41:41.627
And then you named it after her?
That's such a sweet tribute.

41:41.710 --> 41:44.588
- I didn't actually...
- Ice cream!

41:47.549 --> 41:48.926
Hey!

41:56.433 --> 41:59.520
<i>You know, we still haven't been
to the coolest little shop in Brooklyn.</i>

41:59.603 --> 42:02.147
<i>Only real insiders know about it.</i>

42:03.315 --> 42:05.484
<i>And what about you? Why New York?</i>

42:05.567 --> 42:07.319
I followed a man.

42:07.402 --> 42:09.780
Did the man know you were following him?

42:09.863 --> 42:13.617
He did when I snuck into his apartment,
impaled him with an ice pick

42:13.700 --> 42:15.786
and feasted on his remains.

42:15.869 --> 42:17.287
Frightening.

42:17.371 --> 42:19.790
But what's the real reason?

42:23.043 --> 42:27.589
Well, growing up, my mom was
an art history professor at Bard.

42:27.673 --> 42:30.342
So it was winter like 90 months of the year.

42:30.425 --> 42:34.012
So every weekend,
she'd take me to the Hessel Museum.

42:34.096 --> 42:40.310
And she taught me
that art tells stories about people, places,

42:40.394 --> 42:43.105
movements, moments in time.

42:45.190 --> 42:50.112
The coolest thing about my mom is,
she really sees art...

42:50.195 --> 42:53.031
in everything.

42:53.115 --> 42:55.033
Like, anywhere.

42:59.496 --> 43:02.249
What city has more art than New York?

43:07.546 --> 43:12.217
You know, I think this project is really
having a positive impact on me.

43:12.301 --> 43:14.595
I woke up this morning,
my pillow was totally dry.

43:14.678 --> 43:17.097
And then feel my bag. It's so light.

43:17.181 --> 43:21.018
I am growing too.
I have not called you a hoarder today.

43:21.101 --> 43:22.311
Typical man.

43:22.394 --> 43:24.980
Proud of himself for something
that isn't an achievement.

43:25.063 --> 43:27.774
Okay. Good talk. I'm gonna go get a coffee.

43:27.858 --> 43:29.318
Do you want anything?

43:29.401 --> 43:32.154
No, I quit coffee.
Only water or booze for this temple.

43:32.237 --> 43:33.989
I'm Paleo.

43:34.072 --> 43:38.493
- I'm not sure that's what Paleo means.
- No, no. It has to do with nuts.

43:38.577 --> 43:41.663
- Okay. I'm gonna go.
- Okay.

43:44.583 --> 43:46.084
- Hi there.
- Hi.

43:46.168 --> 43:49.630
I'm here for the 72-inch television.

43:49.713 --> 43:53.133
You guys are like
the last book shop on earth, huh?

43:53.217 --> 43:55.135
We're the real deal.
It was my grandfather's.

43:55.219 --> 43:58.931
Oh, okay. Well, I was about
to say something that...

43:59.014 --> 44:01.725
It wouldn't have gone well.
Anyway, thank you so much.

44:01.808 --> 44:04.144
- Have a great day.
- All right.

44:05.145 --> 44:09.566
- Oh, hey! Your case.
- I got it. I know him.

44:22.287 --> 44:24.081
Excuse me. Do you mind?

44:24.164 --> 44:26.750
Move! Oh, my God! Move.

44:27.751 --> 44:31.421
Excuse me. Do you have a moment
for Planned Parenthood? Okay.

44:31.505 --> 44:33.882
Excuse me. Do you have a moment
for Planned Parenthood?

44:33.966 --> 44:35.634
- Yes.
- Thanks.

44:35.717 --> 44:37.511
I gotta go.

44:37.594 --> 44:39.596
Do you have a moment for Planned Parenthood?

44:39.680 --> 44:42.307
Oh, you don't care
about reproductive rights?

44:46.562 --> 44:47.980
It's a first edition.

44:48.063 --> 44:50.399
- No.
- Yeah.

44:50.482 --> 44:52.067
Lucy!

44:54.152 --> 44:55.404
Max!

44:55.487 --> 44:57.155
Hi! Oh, my God.

44:57.239 --> 44:59.491
This is so random.

45:01.118 --> 45:01.952
Hi.

45:04.621 --> 45:05.998
- French.
- Oh, sorry.

45:06.081 --> 45:10.043
I just got back from Paris,
so still in there.

45:10.127 --> 45:12.754
- Right.
- This is Amelia.

45:12.838 --> 45:16.717
You saw her the night that...

45:16.800 --> 45:19.303
Are you okay? I'm a doctor, so...

45:19.386 --> 45:21.930
Me? Me? Me good. Me... I'm great.

45:22.014 --> 45:24.683
Because last time... You know.

45:26.435 --> 45:28.437
Right. That night. Oh, my God.

45:28.520 --> 45:29.646
That was such a fun night.

45:29.730 --> 45:32.858
I was just really living my truth
and, like, enjoying myself.

45:32.941 --> 45:34.318
I'm in my mid-20s.

45:34.401 --> 45:36.278
You know, I barely even wash my face.

45:36.361 --> 45:39.198
And sometimes I moisturize, if I feel fancy.

45:39.281 --> 45:42.117
But I just have the collagen
ready to go. I'm 26, so...

45:42.201 --> 45:44.328
Lucy! Hi.

45:44.411 --> 45:46.413
There you are.

45:47.456 --> 45:49.416
Got the flat white for you.

45:50.459 --> 45:53.629
- I...
- Yeah. I'm her assistant, Nick.

45:53.712 --> 45:55.881
- Hey. I'm Max.
- Hi.

45:55.964 --> 45:59.510
This one really knows
how to treat her staff, you know?

45:59.593 --> 46:01.720
- Staff?
- She didn't tell you?

46:01.803 --> 46:04.681
Lucy started her own gallery.

46:04.765 --> 46:08.185
Yeah. Big deal. I mean,
it's still underground, but it's gonna be...

46:09.186 --> 46:12.481
It's gonna blow up. Big. Big time.
Blowing. Lots of blowing up.

46:12.564 --> 46:14.274
That's...

46:14.358 --> 46:16.109
That's exceptional.

46:16.193 --> 46:18.862
Where is it? I'd love to come visit.

46:18.946 --> 46:22.533
And we would also love you
to come visit sometime,

46:22.616 --> 46:25.160
but we are late
for that meeting with that...

46:25.244 --> 46:28.747
- Meeting. Larry.
- Larry! Larry.

46:28.830 --> 46:30.249
Gagosian?

46:30.332 --> 46:31.333
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

46:31.416 --> 46:33.544
He's like a...
How did you describe him? Like a...

46:33.627 --> 46:36.004
Oh, he's like a post-modern teddy bear.

46:36.088 --> 46:38.257
- Just the sweetest guy.
- Yeah.

46:38.340 --> 46:39.550
You know?

46:39.633 --> 46:41.677
- Oh, yeah.
- Never met him.

46:41.760 --> 46:43.929
- We have to...
- Yeah, he hates it when we're late.

46:44.012 --> 46:45.389
- We should really run.
- He does.

46:45.472 --> 46:47.599
- But great to see you.
- Nice to meet you.

46:49.226 --> 46:51.353
Gagosian? Okay.

46:51.436 --> 46:53.063
Shit.

46:54.690 --> 46:56.900
He's just moved on. It's...

46:56.984 --> 46:59.528
Why is it so hard for me
and so easy for him?

46:59.611 --> 47:03.240
- Am I that forgettable?
- Are you kidding me? Max aches for you.

47:03.323 --> 47:07.327
He said so himself.
You're the wild card, the fun, the sparkle.

47:07.411 --> 47:11.248
- You think so?
- I... He thinks so.

47:11.331 --> 47:13.000
- Yes.
- Right.

47:14.001 --> 47:17.045
- Come on. Let's go in here.
- Okay.

47:18.046 --> 47:20.799
Do you think Max
and the doctor have moved in together?

47:20.883 --> 47:24.553
No. No, Max likes his personal space, so...

47:25.554 --> 47:28.974
She probably has an amazing
but crazy skin care routine.

47:29.975 --> 47:31.935
What if he likes it?

47:33.228 --> 47:34.813
Wait, where are we?

47:34.897 --> 47:37.441
Great, is this the third attempt at murder?

47:37.524 --> 47:40.944
Can we get it over and done with, please?
Just put me out of my misery.

47:41.028 --> 47:43.530
Hey, Yan. Do your thing.

47:53.874 --> 47:57.544
- What?
- I'll never tire of that reaction.

47:57.628 --> 48:00.464
- Yan.
- Hey, man. How's the hotel going?

48:00.547 --> 48:02.132
Excellent.

48:02.216 --> 48:04.635
Don't listen to her.
She's a glass-half-full kind of gal.

48:04.718 --> 48:08.847
You're right, yeah.
It's better to be a brooding cynic.

48:08.931 --> 48:11.475
Can you please go get my sign?

48:12.518 --> 48:14.561
So he just makes anything in neon?

48:14.645 --> 48:16.605
Yeah, including a blinking sign
over your head

48:16.688 --> 48:19.149
that says "Keep Back 200 Feet."

48:19.233 --> 48:23.737
Check this out. It's gonna look great
hanging in the lobby of the Chloe.

48:24.988 --> 48:29.910
It's Latin for "Into the middle of things."
It's what the hotel stands for.

48:29.993 --> 48:34.665
It's a place where people will meet
and intersect in our story.

48:35.749 --> 48:39.336
The Chloe will always be a place
they stopped along the way.

48:40.337 --> 48:43.507
See? I have feelings.

49:13.412 --> 49:16.665
Remember when I drove my car
into a parked school bus?

49:16.748 --> 49:19.835
Well, I'm not the mess you once knew.

49:19.918 --> 49:22.171
I have my shit together.

49:22.254 --> 49:23.630
Promise.

49:24.631 --> 49:27.801
- Hey. Who was that?
- No one.

49:27.885 --> 49:31.555
Oh, hello, fancy pants.
Where are you off to?

49:31.638 --> 49:34.391
Well, we are going to the bank.

49:34.474 --> 49:37.769
I have that meeting, and I am terrified.

49:37.853 --> 49:39.938
This is it. Make or break, right?

49:40.022 --> 49:43.567
- I'm coming along to play the race card.
- I think it'll be very effective.

49:43.650 --> 49:45.277
- Thank you.
- Look on the bright side.

49:45.360 --> 49:48.322
The gallery is bringing in
a bunch of revenue.

49:48.405 --> 49:51.867
No. I'm cautiously optimistic
in a very negative way.

49:51.950 --> 49:54.328
- I've lost all hope.
- But we should probably...

49:54.411 --> 49:56.330
Wait, wait. Before you go, take a seat.

49:56.413 --> 49:58.248
- I want you to listen to this.
- We're...

49:58.332 --> 50:01.251
No, come on. It'll just take a minute.
It'll be good for you.

50:01.335 --> 50:03.003
I need to share.

50:04.004 --> 50:06.131
"Dwayne and I met on New Year's Eve.

50:06.215 --> 50:07.966
We stole this bottle of champagne

50:08.050 --> 50:10.344
and resolved to drink it together
the next year.

50:10.427 --> 50:13.805
But Dwayne got sick
and next year never came.

50:13.889 --> 50:16.099
Lately, I've found myself drinking alone,

50:16.183 --> 50:20.229
but this is the one bottle
I can't bring myself to open."

50:20.312 --> 50:23.148
Nope. Nope!

50:24.900 --> 50:27.444
- Nick, are you crying?
- Why...?

50:27.528 --> 50:29.154
No. Why would I...? What?

50:29.238 --> 50:31.323
Why wouldn't you cry? Dwayne is dead, dude.

50:31.406 --> 50:34.159
They're about to drink a bottle together
and now he's a ghost.

50:34.243 --> 50:37.412
He didn't ghost him. He's an actual ghost.
Why would you do that to us?

