01:28:56.753 --> 01:28:57.671
Cool.

01:28:58.672 --> 01:29:01.717
Okay. Goodbye. Nice to...

01:29:01.800 --> 01:29:03.594
Jeff. Great.

01:29:30.162 --> 01:29:32.956
Listen, I wanted to tell you that...

01:29:35.375 --> 01:29:37.085
What?

01:29:40.714 --> 01:29:44.426
The Broken Hearts Ball is your night,
and I just wanted you to know that...

01:29:45.427 --> 01:29:48.680
I'm gonna steer clear of the hotel, okay?

01:29:49.681 --> 01:29:52.100
The Chloe Hotel?

01:29:53.560 --> 01:29:57.606
For what it's worth,
I was only showing her around.

01:29:57.689 --> 01:30:04.571
I named the hotel after her a long time ago,
and it got too late and too expensive...

01:30:05.739 --> 01:30:07.574
to change it.

01:30:11.578 --> 01:30:13.539
I'm sorry.

01:30:22.381 --> 01:30:23.841
Okay.

01:30:48.282 --> 01:30:51.785
Many artists have fallen in love with me.

01:30:52.786 --> 01:30:56.874
I didn't see you there.
But, yes, I know about all your lovers.

01:30:57.875 --> 01:31:01.420
That's a very strange thing to say.
Very odd.

01:31:02.421 --> 01:31:06.175
I have something for your installation.

01:31:07.843 --> 01:31:10.679
I married a man
who was jealous about everything.

01:31:10.762 --> 01:31:13.390
If I was enthusiastic about a book,
about a place,

01:31:13.473 --> 01:31:16.185
about a flower, about a human being...

01:31:16.268 --> 01:31:18.061
jealous.

01:31:22.065 --> 01:31:23.567
There's nothing inside.

01:31:23.650 --> 01:31:26.486
I left him. I sold the ring.

01:31:26.570 --> 01:31:28.822
I started the Woolf Gallery,

01:31:28.906 --> 01:31:33.243
and I vowed to represent artists
who made me feel enthusiastic.

01:31:33.327 --> 01:31:34.828
I never looked back.

01:31:37.289 --> 01:31:39.249
Did you regret marrying him?

01:31:39.333 --> 01:31:40.209
Never.

01:31:41.210 --> 01:31:44.379
I wouldn't be me
if our paths hadn't crossed.

01:31:44.463 --> 01:31:47.508
I also wouldn't be me if I hadn't let go.

01:31:49.218 --> 01:31:51.595
Pain, my dear, is inevitable.

01:31:52.596 --> 01:31:57.059
It's what you do with it that matters.

01:32:15.327 --> 01:32:17.871
- Hey, what's up?
- Hey. How you doing?

01:32:17.955 --> 01:32:19.498
What are you doing?

01:32:19.581 --> 01:32:22.251
- Oh, hello! Thank you.
- I've never seen her do that before.

01:32:22.334 --> 01:32:23.794
That's weird.

01:33:20.893 --> 01:33:24.313
I don't really know what I'm doing here.

01:33:25.480 --> 01:33:29.234
I don't know.
I've never been broken up with.

01:33:30.277 --> 01:33:32.112
I don't know what it is about this room,

01:33:32.196 --> 01:33:34.948
but there's something about it
that's so much less...

01:33:35.032 --> 01:33:36.033
"Hoardery"?

01:33:36.116 --> 01:33:40.329
Doesn't look like a homeless woman
just lives here in her free time.

01:33:40.412 --> 01:33:43.415
You know what? I should
throw you guys out in the trash.

01:33:43.498 --> 01:33:45.834
Marie Kondo your asses. How about that?

01:33:45.918 --> 01:33:49.546
- Is Nick coming tonight?
- Yeah. Inquiring minds wanna know.

01:33:49.630 --> 01:33:53.050
Don't know, don't care.
It's my night. I'm just doing me.

01:33:54.343 --> 01:33:55.677
- Fine. Later.
- No, now.

01:33:55.761 --> 01:33:58.222
- You always say later and you never pay.
- I always pay.

01:33:58.305 --> 01:34:01.683
- You owe me so much...
- Pay? Wait, what? What is going on here?

01:34:01.767 --> 01:34:04.770
- What secrets do you hold?
- Nothing.

01:34:04.853 --> 01:34:05.729
Nadine?

01:34:05.812 --> 01:34:08.524
We bet that you
and Nick would get back together.

01:34:08.607 --> 01:34:11.860
I said no. I won, obviously. I always win.

01:34:11.944 --> 01:34:14.363
- You what?
- We bet on all your relationships.

01:34:14.446 --> 01:34:16.198
How do you think I afford this lifestyle?

01:34:16.281 --> 01:34:19.034
- Wait. How much have you bet over the years?
- Like...

01:34:19.117 --> 01:34:20.369
- Pennies.
- Barely anything.

01:34:20.452 --> 01:34:22.663
No, tell me right now. You tell me. You...

01:34:22.746 --> 01:34:25.123
Seven hundred and ninety-eight dollars,
34 cents.

01:34:26.458 --> 01:34:30.379
Now? You choose to speak now?
Oh, we're getting a divorce.

01:34:30.462 --> 01:34:31.505
We were never married.

01:34:31.588 --> 01:34:35.050
Well, hurry up and ask me
so I can fricking divorce you already!

01:34:37.177 --> 01:34:39.388
- Will you marry me?
- Get out!

01:34:39.471 --> 01:34:43.684
That's why I think possums are pretty much
the coolest animal in the entire world.

01:34:43.767 --> 01:34:47.396
But if you're gonna have possums in there,
meerkats need to be in the conversation.

01:34:47.479 --> 01:34:50.232
They can stand up on hind legs like this,
looking around everywhere.

01:34:50.315 --> 01:34:53.610
They also can run on four legs.
Feed them bugs if they were your pet.

01:34:53.694 --> 01:34:54.903
They run around in the desert.

01:34:54.987 --> 01:34:57.990
Don't touch that jerky.
It's too close to the bug spray.

01:34:58.991 --> 01:35:01.827
- So you're really not coming?
- I don't know, man.

01:35:01.910 --> 01:35:04.705
Don't feel well and I'm worried
about the hotel opening and...

01:35:04.788 --> 01:35:07.124
I think I'm coming down
with a fever. So, yeah.

01:35:07.207 --> 01:35:09.126
Do you mind feeling my forehead?

01:35:09.209 --> 01:35:10.794
- It's really hot, right?
- You're fine.

01:35:10.878 --> 01:35:11.837
That's what I thought.

01:35:11.920 --> 01:35:14.131
We have to go.
I didn't put heels on to show up late.

01:35:14.214 --> 01:35:17.301
Real comforting.
You guys are gonna be great parents.

01:35:17.384 --> 01:35:20.846
A sick man disgusts me. You need
to explain to him what's going on.

01:35:20.929 --> 01:35:23.098
No, I don't. He's a moron. Look at him.

01:35:23.182 --> 01:35:24.558
Like you're so evolved?

01:35:24.641 --> 01:35:27.686
- All men are morons. We let you run things.
- Not the humanity speech.

01:35:27.769 --> 01:35:30.981
You ruined the planet, started wars,
killed the bees. You raped and pillaged.

01:35:31.064 --> 01:35:33.650
And if you opened your eyes
to what was going on in the world,

01:35:33.734 --> 01:35:35.485
you'd never stop crying.

01:35:36.653 --> 01:35:39.031
I feel I had nothing to do with that,
but I will take it.

01:35:39.114 --> 01:35:41.575
As far as men go?
He's way stupider than I am.

01:35:41.658 --> 01:35:44.745
You do realize I'm standing right here
and I can hear you?

01:35:44.828 --> 01:35:46.246
Yeah, well, I pointed at you.

01:35:46.330 --> 01:35:49.333
Listen up. You're not sick.
You need to tell him what's going on.

01:35:49.416 --> 01:35:50.792
- No, I don't.
- I will be outside.

01:35:50.876 --> 01:35:53.295
- Can you please come back?
- We're not going to be late!

01:35:53.378 --> 01:35:54.922
All right.

01:35:56.006 --> 01:35:59.009
- Nick, you're not sick, buddy.
- Oh, I feel very ill.

01:35:59.092 --> 01:36:01.678
- Right. You're heartbroken, bro.
- No, I'm not.

01:36:01.762 --> 01:36:04.806
- Yeah, you are.
- No, I'm not.

01:36:06.517 --> 01:36:10.145
- Where do you think the money came from?
- I don't know. Where did...? What?

01:36:10.229 --> 01:36:12.773
- The loan that saved your ass.
- Yes?

01:36:12.856 --> 01:36:16.735
- The hotel you named after another woman?
- What about it?

01:36:16.818 --> 01:36:19.655
Remember
that mysterious private lender, Nick?

01:36:20.822 --> 01:36:23.951
Lucy convinced Eva Woolf
to float you the money, man.

01:36:24.034 --> 01:36:26.995
She saved your ass.
It's like she's your knight in shining armor

01:36:27.079 --> 01:36:29.289
and you're the stupidest princess
I have ever met.

01:36:29.373 --> 01:36:31.917
No. You know what?
I'm not a stupid princess. Take these.

01:36:32.000 --> 01:36:35.003
I didn't mean it literally.
Don't take offense.

01:36:35.087 --> 01:36:37.673
Oh, so I'll just pay for this...?

01:36:54.189 --> 01:36:57.442
I can't believe you did this
with your crazy.

01:36:57.526 --> 01:36:59.570
My crazy is beautiful.

01:36:59.653 --> 01:37:01.446
Crazy beautiful.

01:37:02.447 --> 01:37:05.450
I mean, team spirit or... What?
I don't know. Where's Jeff?

01:37:05.534 --> 01:37:09.997
I hate him. I love him. I mean, I hate him.
What are you doing to me?

01:37:10.080 --> 01:37:11.623
How's this?

01:37:11.707 --> 01:37:14.001
- My body's not rejecting it.
- No?

01:37:14.084 --> 01:37:15.252
No, that's too much. Don't.

01:38:14.186 --> 01:38:16.647
Hello, hoarders and art freaks.

01:38:16.730 --> 01:38:19.274
Welcome to the Broken Heart Gallery.

01:38:21.777 --> 01:38:25.155
Yes! Yes.

01:38:25.239 --> 01:38:28.909
This gallery does not have
hundred-thousand-dollar paintings

01:38:28.992 --> 01:38:30.869
or precious sculptures.

01:38:30.953 --> 01:38:35.290
It has... crap. A lot of it.

01:38:36.291 --> 01:38:39.253
But these are the things we keep,

01:38:39.336 --> 01:38:43.841
the souvenirs that tell the stories
of our lives,

01:38:43.924 --> 01:38:47.094
even if that is a half-eaten crab cake.

01:38:50.806 --> 01:38:52.975
- Hey, I need that order.
- I thought you canceled it.

01:38:53.058 --> 01:38:55.978
- Yeah. Can you un-cancel it?
- Yeah.

01:38:56.061 --> 01:38:57.771
I began collecting

01:38:57.855 --> 01:39:01.108
because I lost someone a long time ago.

01:39:02.067 --> 01:39:05.696
Her body is still here,
but her memory is gone.

01:39:07.614 --> 01:39:10.242
<i>So, in many ways, she is gone too.</i>

01:39:11.243 --> 01:39:13.287
My mother was my first heartbreak.

01:39:14.997 --> 01:39:21.086
I was afraid I would end up like her,
that I would forget and be forgotten.

01:39:22.254 --> 01:39:26.967
<i>So I clung to things,
which kept me from moving forward.</i>

01:39:27.968 --> 01:39:31.930
Heartbreak is the loneliest,
most isolating feeling in the world.

01:39:32.014 --> 01:39:34.892
<i>And the truth is, it happens to us all.</i>

01:39:36.018 --> 01:39:38.353
It is the great equalizer.

01:39:39.479 --> 01:39:43.483
And without heartbreak,
I wouldn't have built this place.

01:39:44.484 --> 01:39:49.907
So, I guess, in the end,
the thing that broke me...

01:39:49.990 --> 01:39:51.783
also made me whole.

01:39:51.867 --> 01:39:55.829
Lucy! Sorry. Excuse me. Sorry.

01:39:57.289 --> 01:39:58.415
Sorry.

01:39:58.498 --> 01:40:00.250
Okay.

01:40:02.002 --> 01:40:03.587
Lucy.

01:40:05.422 --> 01:40:08.467
So I'd like to direct your attention
to some of the installations...

01:40:08.550 --> 01:40:10.260
Lucy!

01:40:11.345 --> 01:40:14.348
Well, this is awkward.

01:40:14.431 --> 01:40:16.600
Nick! What are you doing?

01:40:16.683 --> 01:40:20.687
What does it look like?
It's... It's a grand gesture.

01:40:22.814 --> 01:40:24.316
This is kind of a bad time.

01:40:24.399 --> 01:40:27.444
If you just wanna wait patiently, quietly,
until I'm done...

01:40:27.528 --> 01:40:29.196
No. No, I can't do that.

01:40:32.115 --> 01:40:33.909
The map was mine.

01:40:35.702 --> 01:40:37.621
- Wait. What?
- The map.

01:40:38.622 --> 01:40:41.834
I put the map in here. I know I said he...

01:40:42.835 --> 01:40:46.380
<i>It's kind of random. I don't know.
I was just trying to throw you off.</i>

01:40:46.463 --> 01:40:50.884
I met Chloe working at a hotel.
And she was...

01:40:50.968 --> 01:40:52.469
I fell in love with her.

01:40:53.595 --> 01:40:56.181
And then she left me for my boss.

01:40:57.182 --> 01:40:58.433
And I was devastated.

01:40:59.434 --> 01:41:03.897
And I promised myself that I would never
let anyone make me feel that way again.

01:41:04.898 --> 01:41:06.400
And then I met you.

01:41:07.401 --> 01:41:13.323
And so I put the map on the wall
because I wanted to see you again.

01:41:16.702 --> 01:41:19.121
Could have just asked me
to dinner or something.

01:41:19.204 --> 01:41:21.790
- Yeah. In hindsight.
- Next time.

01:41:21.874 --> 01:41:23.834
Probably. Good thing, you know?

01:41:25.335 --> 01:41:31.466
But love makes you do crazy,
stupid, irrational things, and...

01:41:31.550 --> 01:41:37.681
And I guess what I'm trying to say,
Lucy, is I love you.

01:41:49.776 --> 01:41:52.196
Try it again. Try it again.

01:41:52.279 --> 01:41:54.198
I love you, Lucy.

01:41:54.281 --> 01:41:57.367
Yeah, I heard you.
Gonna get back to my speech now.

01:41:59.786 --> 01:42:01.079
Maybe I should just...

01:42:01.163 --> 01:42:03.957
- You should stay.
- Sort of awkward that you're not...

01:42:04.041 --> 01:42:05.667
Oh, my God.

01:42:05.751 --> 01:42:07.586
Love him back! Right?

01:42:07.669 --> 01:42:13.175
- Yeah, I think you should love him back.
- You should love him back.

01:42:13.258 --> 01:42:17.513
I know that was sweet, but you don't know
what the context is, so...

01:42:17.596 --> 01:42:19.598
- Love him back.
- Love him back!

01:42:19.681 --> 01:42:24.353
- <i>Love him back! Love him back!</i>
- Oh, we're chanting? We're chanting now.

01:42:24.436 --> 01:42:28.148
- <i>Love him back! Love him back!</i>
- Whoa, okay. Okay, this is...

01:42:28.232 --> 01:42:31.193
<i>Love him back! Love him back!</i>

01:42:31.276 --> 01:42:34.488
Okay, enough! Be quiet.

01:42:46.917 --> 01:42:51.088
Just... Excuse me. Thank you, excuse me.

01:42:57.261 --> 01:42:58.095
Hi.

01:42:59.096 --> 01:43:02.349
I'm a lump of coal. I feel nothing.

01:43:07.104 --> 01:43:09.773
{\an8}I changed the name of the hotel.

01:43:10.858 --> 01:43:13.110
{\an8}It's no big deal.

01:43:20.742 --> 01:43:25.664
Okay, if I didn't do this, they would
all turn on me, so this is for them.

01:43:35.883 --> 01:43:39.011
You're the only person
I didn't collect anything from.

01:43:40.012 --> 01:43:40.846
Why's that?

01:43:41.847 --> 01:43:44.558
Because I love you too.

01:43:45.809 --> 01:43:48.061
Okay, okay.

01:44:51.834 --> 01:44:56.755
Okay. Hi. Okay...

01:44:58.799 --> 01:45:01.718
This is the bottle
from the first whiskey we shared together.

01:45:01.802 --> 01:45:06.807
And this is the pen Lucy used
to defile my hotel,

01:45:08.183 --> 01:45:12.271
and this is the hotel room key from
when Lucy and I first started connecting...

01:45:12.354 --> 01:45:13.981
What are you doing?

01:45:14.064 --> 01:45:17.943
I'm doing the thing about the stuff,
you know, that the other people did.

01:45:18.944 --> 01:45:20.779
I'm sorry. She has no manners.

01:45:20.863 --> 01:45:24.116
Okay, that's cute, but you don't need this

01:45:24.199 --> 01:45:26.118
because we're never breaking up.

01:45:26.201 --> 01:45:27.619
Not even in a zombie apocalypse.

01:45:27.703 --> 01:45:30.372
I'm sorry, he's such a hoarder.

01:45:30.455 --> 01:45:34.209
We don't use that term. It's derogatory.

01:45:34.293 --> 01:45:36.920
No, taught you so well.
